Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper discusses knowledge graph embedding models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) tasks. 
2. cs.LG - The paper proposes a novel embedding model and compares its performance with other state-of-the-art approaches, which falls under the category of machine learning and specifically, learning on graphs. 
3. cs.CL - The paper discusses the problem of missing facts in knowledge graphs, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics. 
4. cs.DB - The paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are commonly used in databases and information retrieval systems. 
5. cs.DS - The paper discusses the scalability of the proposed model to large-size knowledge graphs, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms.
